cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper deals with a specific family of programming languages, namely operator precedence languages, and proposes a new temporal logic suitable for expressing and verifying properties of these languages. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper presents a new temporal logic and proves its expressiveness and decidability properties. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory): The paper discusses the automata-theoretic aspects of the proposed logic, including the construction of an automaton recognizing the sentences satisfying a given formula. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper mentions the original motivation of the inventor of operator precedence languages, which was to support efficient parsing, i.e. building the hidden syntax tree of language sentences. This involves data structures and algorithms for parsing. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper proposes a new approach to model checking for a specific family of programming languages, which has potential applications in software engineering.
